frus:attachment.p:
No. 23, Louisa Weingerten, twenty-eight, Swiss vagrant and prostitute;
                            transportation to the United States provided her and two others of same
                            character by the Swiss Government, which required of them to sign papers
                            releasing the said Government from any further claims; landed at Quebec;
                            returned March 10, 1882, through State board of charities. * * *
